id: pmc-ek6t
title: Publish pm-changelog to npm after registry authentication
description: "The package is release-ready and npm publish dry-run succeeds, but the actual npm publish command cannot complete because this machine is not authenticated to the npm registry. Publication must be retried after npm login or an npm automation token is configured."
type: Issue
status: blocked
priority: 0
tags[3]: blocked,npm,release
created_at: "2026-05-23T19:36:09.869Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T19:36:09.869Z"
deadline: "2026-05-23T00:00:00.000Z"
assignee: steve
author: codex
estimated_minutes: 20
acceptance_criteria: "- npm whoami succeeds against https://registry.npmjs.org/.\\n- npm publish --access public completes for pm-changelog@0.1.0 or the next available release version.\\n- npm view pm-changelog version returns the published version.\\n- pm install npm:pm-changelog --project succeeds in a clean temporary pm project and pm changelog generate works from that install path."
reviewer: steve
risk: high
confidence: high
sprint: 2026-05-release
release: 0.1.0
reporter: codex
severity: high
environment: local shell npm registry
repro_steps: Run npm whoami or npm publish --access public from /home/steve/container/pm-packages/pm-changelog.
expected_result: "pm-changelog is published publicly to npm and installable via pm install npm:pm-changelog --project."
actual_result: "npm publish --dry-run succeeds with the 25-file package payload, but npm publish --access public fails with ENEEDAUTH because the machine is not logged in to npm."
component: npm-publication
